definitions.definition: A surname from Welsh [in turn originating as a patronymic] , anglicized from ap Rhys .

subdefinitions.definition: A place in the United States : An unincorporated community in Queen Anne's County , Maryland . A township in Monroe County , Pennsylvania . An unincorporated community in Rusk County , Texas . A city , the county seat of Carbon County , Utah . A river in Utah , United States . An unincorporated community in Monongalia County , West Virginia . A town in Langlade County , Wisconsin . An unincorporated community in Garfield , Jackson County , Wisconsin .
A village municipality in La Mitis regional county municipality, Bas-Saint-Laurent region, Quebec , Canada .
A town in Yorke Peninsula council area, South Australia .
